ed at redder wavelengths, which are more sensitive to\nthe old stellar population that dominates the stellar mass of the galaxies. The\nslope is unchanged when GeMS $K_s$-band imaging is degraded to the resolution\nof $K$-band HST/NICMOS resolution but dramatically affected when degraded to\n$K_s$-band Magellan/FourStar resolution. Such measurements must be made with AO\nin order to accurately characterise the sizes of compact, $z$ = 1 galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Sep 2016 08:29:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 22 Sep 2016 04:17:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-23"}
