n^2$ term, and\nthe transport coefficients $c_V$ and $c_T$, describing the leading $\\sim V^2$\nand $\\sim T^2$ terms in the nonlinear differential conductance. A sign change\nin $c_A$ or $c_V$ is indicative of a change from a local maximum to a local\nminimum in the spectral function or nonlinear conductance, respectively, as is\nexpected to occur when an increasing magnetic field causes the Kondo resonance\nto split into two subpeaks. We find that the fields $B_A$, $B_T$ and $B_V$ at\nwhich $c_A$, $c_T$ and $c_V$ change sign, respectively, are all of order $T_K$,\nas expected, with $B_A = B_T = B_V = 0.75073\\,T_K$ in the Kondo limit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Sep 2016 13:42:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 21 Dec 2017 10:29:16 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 17 Jul 2018 11:58:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-09"}
